  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN150.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">pakaṟkuṟi vantu kaṇṇuṟṟu nīṅkun talaimakaṉait tōḻi talaimakaṉai yetirppaṭṭu niṉṟu ceṟippaṟivuṟīi varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">How the confidante encountered [and] stood [before] HIM, who had come to the day tryst, met [HER and] left, [and how she] informed HIM of [HER] confinement [and] urged for marriage.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN150.2">
            <lg type="edition">
              <l>piṉṉuviṭa neṟinta kūntalum poṉṉeṉa</l>
              <l>vākat tarumpiya cuṇaṅkum vampuviṭa</l>
              <l>kaṇṇurut teḻunta mulaiyu nōkki</l>
              <l>yelliṉai periteṉap paṉmāṇ kūṟip</l>
              <l>peruntō ḷaṭaiya muyaṅki nīṭuniṉain</l>
              <l>taruṅkaṭip paṭuttaṉaḷ yāyē kaṭuñcelal</l>
              <l>vāṭcuṟā vaḻaṅkum vaḷaimēy peruntuṟaik</l>
              <l>ka<supplied>ṉai</supplied>tta neytaṟ kaṇpōṉ māmalar</l>
              <l>naṉainta ceruntip pōtuvā yaviḻa</l>
              <l>mālai maṇiyitaḻ kūmpak kālaik</l>
              <l>kaṇṇāṟu kāviyoṭu kaṇṇeṉa malaruṅ</l>
              <l>kaḻiyuṅ kāṉaluṅ kāṇṭoṟum palapulantu</l>
              <l>vārār kolleṉap paruvan</l>
              <l>tārār mārpanī tanta ñāṉṟē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <l>Looking at [her] curling tresses, when the braids came loose,</l>
                <l>at [her] beauty spots that have budded like gold, and at [her] breasts</l>
                <l>that rise, the nipples taking shape, when the bodice came loose, (1-3)</l>
                <l>saying many times “your [are] very splendid”, (4)</l>
                <l>closely embracing your wide shoulders, thinking long, (5)</l>
                <l>mother did ordain heavy protection, (6)</l>
                <l>− at the time you gave [for your return], you with a chest full of garlands, (14)</l>
                <l>a season when she said “he won’t come”, (13)</l>
                <l>being much vexed each time she saw the seashore grove and the backwaters, (12)</l>
                <l>where the eye-like huge flowers of the blue waterlily that matured (8)</l>
                <l>by the big ghat foraged by mussels, where swift-going swordfish roam, (6d-7)</l>
                <l>bloom like eyes along with the blue lotus, fragrant with nectar, (11)</l>
                <l>in the morning when [its] sapphire petals close, in the evening (10)</l>
                <l>when the bud mouths open on the pear-tree that had become wet. (9)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
